{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"26354238-22e5-4f6a-9ed1-497568f566f4","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed **above** them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_xzfxdDM64HXbfjHQ8XZkqG","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-d640b9cb59af464e98c7cc15800f61a1/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-d640b9cb59af464e98c7cc15800f61a1/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"4f941271-9a3b-4789-a1d8-db704dacfe14","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *above* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines types\n3. `Program.fs` — uses both\n\nThe fix is to put `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":365,"requestId":"5C1A:3E5509:5CBD0E9:659501B:69F15687"},"id":"c3416a55-1601-40e0-b019-dcadc57f5bb6","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:53:34.440Z","parentId":"a2fe3537-347a-4617-b586-4ba326a6ca1b"}
